# Tumor Purity and Ploidy Analysis

Includes both ABSOLUTE and sequenza methods.

## ABSOLUTE

Estimate tumor purity and ploidy from CNV segment data.

### Input file format (.seg)
```
ID  chrom   loc.start   loc.end num.mark    seg.mean
sample1 chr1    1000    2000    50  0.5
```

### Usage
```bash
Rscript run_absolute.R --seg sample.seg --name sample_name --outdir output_dir
```

### Parameters
- `--seg`: Segment file path
- `--name`: Sample name
- `--outdir`: Output directory
- `--disease`: Disease type (default: BLCA)
- `--min.ploidy`: Minimum ploidy (default: 0.5)
- `--max.ploidy`: Maximum ploidy (default: 8)

## sequenza

Estimate tumor purity and ploidy from WGS/WES data.

### Input files
Seqz files processed by sequenza-utils

### Usage
```bash
Rscript run_sequenza.R <sample_name> <input.seqz.gz> <output_dir>
```

## Dependencies

- R packages: ABSOLUTE, numDeriv, optparse, sequenza
